09 Sep 2015 20:56






I would like to think that this would have been just as successful if it had just been an anomalous circus and not this particular GoI anomalous circus. One of the many reasons I dislike GoIs; articles get immediately pigeonholed according to subject matter and then saddled with extraneous context and associations that, in my estimation, have yet to contribute positively to a piece.

With that out of the way, this was far more charming than it had any right to be. My enjoyment blew way past my (admittedly low) silliness threshold for this one. The sheer amount of joy this guy gets out of being a dancing skeleton-person with a cat sidekick was impossible to ignore. The exceedingly goofy performance at the end was exactly the kind of thing I would imagine this guy enjoying, and served as a nice payoff to the article.

Nicely realized, genuinely entertaining article.





